{
  "texts": [
    "Lentivirus generation.",
    "Low-passage HEK 293T cells in 150 mm dishes were grown to 70-90% confluence and transfected using a PEI-based method.",
    "Briefly, for each transfection reaction purified plasmid DNAs (4 µg pMD2.G, 6 µg pSPAX2 and 8 µg Library plasmid) were diluted in 1 mL serum-free DMEM and mixed gently.",
    "Then, 80 µL PEI was added to the DNA-DMEM solution, mixed gently, and incubated for 20 minutes at room temperature.",
    "The resulting DNA-DMEM-PEI solution was added dropwise to 293T cells, which were then returned to the incubator overnight."
  ]
}